Business Brief -- Northrop Corp.:
   Dismissal of 1,000 Workers
   In Aircraft Unit Is Slated
Northrop's aircraft division employed just under 12,000
workers at the end of 1991 in plants in El Segundo,
Hawthorne, Anaheim and Torrance, Calif. The division builds
fuselages for the Boeing 747 aircraft, missiles, unmanned
vehicles and portions of the Navy Hornet strike fighter.